### Prisma Migrations Strategy for Teams

Implement migration workflows: 1) Developers create migrations locally with `prisma migrate dev`, 2) Commit migrations to git, 3) CI/CD runs `prisma migrate deploy` before app startup, 4) Rollback strategy using `prisma migrate resolve`.

Use shadow databases for CI testing to validate migrations without touching production. Enable `--create-only` flag for reviewing migrations before applying. Document rollback procedures and maintain migration version history.

```typescript
// prisma/.env.test
DATABASE_URL="postgresql://..._shadow"

// CI/CD pipeline (GitHub Actions)
- name: Run migrations
  run: npx prisma migrate deploy
  env:
    DATABASE_URL: ${{ secrets.DATABASE_URL }}

// Validate in test environment
- name: Validate migrations
  run: npx prisma migrate deploy
  env:
    DATABASE_URL: ${{ secrets.SHADOW_DATABASE_URL }}

// Rollback if needed
npx prisma migrate resolve --rolled-back "20240101120000_migration_name"```


**Common interview trap:** Assume migrations always succeed—they don't. Plan for rollbacks, data conflicts, and failed deployments. Lock table during migrations to prevent concurrent writes. Test long-running migrations impact on production.

answer.ru:
